perfcenter.simulator.metric

Class TimeAverageMetric

  • java.lang.Object
    • perfcenter.simulator.metric.MetricSim
      • perfcenter.simulator.metric.TimeAverageMetric

  • public class TimeAverageMetric
extends MetricSim
    This class of hierarchy is used to manage values of a metric which is averaged in a continuous way.

    For example, response time values are recorded once per request completion, and thats discrete, not continuous. On the other hand, utilization is recorded continuously and then averaged.

    The top level class TimeAverageMetric has the information at the level of the cyclic workload slots. The next level _TimeAverageMetricSingleSlot manages the server level bifurcation of the data for the given slot. The lowest level _TimeAverageMetricLowestLevel manages the discrete data for the given slot and given server.

    Author:
    bhavin
